  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-02-07",
    "date": "2022-05-23T21:39:36Z",
    "text": "Equal Access to Therapeutics Act\n\nThis bill prohibits using race or ethnicity as a factor in decisions about an individual's access to COVID-19 treatments (e.g., monoclonal antibody therapies).\n\nSpecifically, the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) may not adopt any policy or guidance that allows race or ethnicity to be factored into such decisions. Furthermore, the Secretary of HHS shall be personally liable for the death of any individual who is denied access to COVID-19 treatments pursuant to a prohibited policy or guidance.\n\nThe bill also prohibits hospitals or other health care providers that have policies restricting access to COVID-19 treatments based on race or ethnicity from receiving federal funds."
  },
